OL,3,CMan jailed for life for 'aiding and
OL,4,Cabetting' murder
OL,6,FAs all four defendants sat in the dock
OL,7,Fon Monday, a barrister for one of the
OL,8,Faccused addressed Mr Justice Fowler.
OL,10,FGavan Duffy KC asked that his client,
OL,11,FAndrew Thomas Kenneth Martin, be re-
OL,12,Farraigned on the murder charge.
OL,14,FFrom Bridge Street in Banbridge,
OL,15,FMartin confirmed his identity to a
OL,16,Fcourt clerk and was then charged with
OL,17,Fmurdering Mr McKeown.
OL,19,FWhen asked how he pleaded to the
OL,20,Fcharge, Martin replied "guilty to
OL,21,Faiding and abetting."
OL,1,Wj5k7j5                          G2/5
